<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dataout-org/ontology/v1.0.0/ontology.ttl> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/created> "2026-07-16"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> <https://dataout.org/> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "This ontology is intended to represent data on SOGIESC-based crimes and discrimination, as well as processes associated with the collection of such data. The idea behind the Dataout Ontology is to represent instances of human rights violations as phenomena that may be observed in different sources, such as court cases or mass-media publications. There are two main components: the provenance information of an incident and its content. Each observed incident is modelled as an instance of Monitoring Record, resulting from Monitoring Activity. A monitoring record connects to the content and metadata of an incident. There are also controlled vocabularies intended for categorising instances. This ontology introduces custom classes and properties and reuses the PROV Ontology, Schema.org, and DCMI Metadata Terms."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/ontology/bibo/doi> "10.5281/zenodo.21393602" .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/preferredNamespacePrefix> "dataout"@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/preferredNamespaceUri> <https://dataout.org/ontology#> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Dataout Ontology"@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "1.0.0"@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#> <https://schema.org/image> <https://github.com/dataout-org/ontology/blob/main/ontology_scheme.png?raw=true> .
