# https://dataout.org/ontology#concernsLegalArticle
<https://dataout.org/ontology#concernsLegalArticle> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#concernsLegalArticle> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#MonitoringRecord> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#concernsLegalArticle> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://schema.org/Legislation> .
<https://schema.org/Legislation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#concernsLegalArticle> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connect a monitoring record to a legal article. Useful when monitoring state persecution."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#concernsLegalArticle> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "concerns legal article"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#defendantCategory
<https://dataout.org/ontology#defendantCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#defendantCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Defendant> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#defendantCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#defendantCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a defendant to its category."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#defendantCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "defendant category"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#hasDefendant
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasDefendant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasDefendant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#MonitoringRecord> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasDefendant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Defendant> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasDefendant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A natural person or legal entity, which is referred to as a defendant in a source documents (for example, a court decision or a mass media publication)."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasDefendant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has defendant"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#hasPenalty
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasPenalty> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasPenalty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#MonitoringRecord> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasPenalty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Penalty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasPenalty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a penalty imposed on a defendant by an official body (a court) to a monitoring record, in which it was mentioned."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasPenalty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has penalty"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#hasTriggerObject
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasTriggerObject> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasTriggerObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#MonitoringRecord> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasTriggerObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://dataout.org/ontology#TriggerObject> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasTriggerObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a trigger object to a monitoring record, in which it was mentioned."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#hasTriggerObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has trigger object"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#mentionedIn
<https://dataout.org/ontology#mentionedIn> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#mentionedIn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#MonitoringRecord> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#mentionedIn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Source> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#mentionedIn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Used to connect a monitoring record to a source that mentions some information about a monitoring record."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#mentionedIn> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "mentioned in"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#monitoringCategory
<https://dataout.org/ontology#monitoringCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#monitoringCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#MonitoringActivity> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#monitoringCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#monitoringCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a monitoring activity to its category."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#monitoringCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "category of monitoring"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyCategory
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Penalty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a penalty to its category."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "penalty category"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyValue
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Penalty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://schema.org/StructuredValue> .
<https://schema.org/StructuredValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a penalty to its value. The value of this property can be a triple, which indicates its quantitative unit (such as a monetary amount or days) and amount. For example, a penalty value could be a quantitative unit of 10 days if the penalty category is detention."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#penaltyValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "penalty value"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#sourceCategory
<https://dataout.org/ontology#sourceCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#sourceCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#Source> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#sourceCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#sourceCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Connects a source to its category."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#sourceCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "source category"@en .
# 
# https://dataout.org/ontology#triggerObjectCategory
<https://dataout.org/ontology#triggerObjectCategory> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#triggerObjectCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://dataout.org/ontology#TriggerObject> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#triggerObjectCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#triggerObjectCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Categories of trigger objects describe what such object is (for example, a film, a social media post, a protest), but not its legal interpretation by authorities."@en .
<https://dataout.org/ontology#triggerObjectCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "trigger object category"@en .
