# 
# https://dataout.org/
<https://dataout.org/> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://dataout.org/> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Organization> .
<https://dataout.org/> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://schema.org/NGO> .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/address> "The Hague, the Netherlands"@en .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/alternateName> "Dataout"@en .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/description> "Dataout is a nonprofit dedicated to uncovering discrimination and crimes based on SOGIESC – sexual orientation, gender identity & expression, and sex characteristics. By conducting research and releasing open data, we aim to empower journalists, researchers, human rights advocates, and policymakers in creating a better social and legal environment for LGBTQIA+ people and others affected by SOGIESC-based discrimination. We focus on the regions where these issues are severe and least visible."@en .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/email> <mailto:contact@dataout.org> .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/legalName> "Dataout Foundation"@en .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/legalName> "Stichting Dataout"@nl .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/name> "Dataout Foundation"@en .
<https://dataout.org/> <https://schema.org/url> <https://dataout.org/> .
